node.text:
It’s very special living in something you hand built with the love of your life (@jacobwitzling). That said it’s only 90 sq ft, so don’t let this video fool you...it can be hard too 😉. But most of the time its just really really great ❤️
.
Cabin by @jacobwitzling and me 🤗
.
#cabinlife #cabin #cabininthewoods #tinyhouse #tinyhousenation #tinyhousemovement #beautifuldestinations #pnw #pnwonderland

node.title: Morning to evening, coffee to wine, in our diamond cabin.

node.text: It’s honestly so fun!!! #AD Go to their page to get it on Amazon Prime *from the makers of @whatdoyoumeme*

In this episode we build the model for The Castle Cabin! This episode was so awesome we had to break it into two parts. Part 2 will be released in a few days, when the building begins!!!!
Special thanks to @adlerstudios for filming, producing, and editing this entire episode. He’s Superman!!!
Time lapse and drone work by @nnaaoo.tt
.
#cabinlife #cabin #diy #tinyhouse #construction #pnw #pnwonderland

node.text:
Season 2 has begun! In this first episode @jacobwitzling and I take you on a tour of the property and show you the hippie hot tub, the outdoor shower, 3 cabins, and everything else we've done over the past 8 months. We hope you enjoy!

Special Thanks to:
@adlerstudios - Cinematography, Directing and Production
@nnaaoo.tt - Time lapse and addition aerial footage
.
.
.
#cabinland #cabinlife #diy #cabin #pnw #tinyhouse

node.text: SWIPE 🤗 With pretty much all the work on our Castle Cabin complete, we have been able to get out more and experience our favorite pastime; hiking! Central Oregon is one of the places we love to visit the most and being atop Mt. Tumalo, on the traditional land of The Confederated Tribes of Warm Springs, with epic views of the Cascades, was stunning. However, I couldn’t help but feel anxious about how dry everything was this early in the season. We are killing the planet. The report released today by the Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change shows irrefutably that global warming and therefore climate change, is stimulated by humans and that even with drastic measures taken, we’re pretty much f*cked. That is not a call to for us to give up, but for us to get our sh*t together and take this thing seriously. We need to demand that the governments and corporations (coal, oil, gas, etc) that are facilitating the destruction of the planet, change. The individual choices we make are important and I have seriously been reevaluating some of mine. These can be the catalyst but if the companies and regulations do not get drastically altered then we have little to no hope

node.text:
1 or 2? 🙃 The loft of our Castle Cabin is complete, and it’s the comfiest room in the house! This was the last space that needed to be finished. So that means our house is done?!? What?!? It took us a little less than two years. I can’t wait to share the final product with y’all soon!
Cabin by @jacobwitzling & @saraunderwood
.
#cabin #interiordesign #woodworking

node.text:
👨🏻‍🦳How do vegans get their protein?
🗣 B*tch peas!
...lol, no but for real, give vegan food a chance, it’s bloody delicious. And if you’re in LA try out my restaurant that I’m a co-owner of @sugartaco, it’s stupid good. Don’t forget to treat yourself to a margarita and donut too 😊 you deserve it after this last year! #vegan #veganfood

Rocking my new @fashionnova suit and showing you how we use our hippie hot tub. One commonly asked question that I forgot to add in the vid is “doesn’t it burn your b00ty?” We added a removable wooden seat in the tub which protects us from the hot bottom (the sides don’t get hot). Fashionnovapartner
.
#woodfirehottub #diy #wildernessculture #beautifuldestinations #pnw #pnwonderland #cabinlife
